Eyes normal. Winged. Male ventrites with a pair of posterior projections.Apex of the right lobe of the aedeagus seemingly subquadrate in dorsal or ventral views (
<figureCitation box="[946,1110,1763,1790]" captionStart="FIGURES 196–208" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1369,1394]" captionTargetBox="[161,1376,279,1341]" captionTargetId="figure@41.[151,1388,265,1349]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 196–208. Adelopsis bruchi (Pic, 1926), 196–201, lectotype male in MNHN, from Buenos Aires. 196, aedeagus, frontal view of aedeagus apex; 197, last ventrite; 198, antenna, dorsal view; 199, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 200, protarsus and protibia; 201, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 202–206, paralectotype male in MACN (same data). 202–205, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views; 206, genital segment; 207–208, paralectotype female in MNHN (same data), spermatheca, in different views. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 196, 197, 202–208; b for figs. 198–201." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542809" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542809/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Figs. 203, 205</figureCitation>
), but clearly pointy, subtriangular in frontal view (
<figureCitation box="[397,495,1800,1827]" captionStart="FIGURES 196–208" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1369,1394]" captionTargetBox="[161,1376,279,1341]" captionTargetId="figure@41.[151,1388,265,1349]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 196–208. Adelopsis bruchi (Pic, 1926), 196–201, lectotype male in MNHN, from Buenos Aires. 196, aedeagus, frontal view of aedeagus apex; 197, last ventrite; 198, antenna, dorsal view; 199, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 200, protarsus and protibia; 201, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 202–206, paralectotype male in MACN (same data). 202–205, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views; 206, genital segment; 207–208, paralectotype female in MNHN (same data), spermatheca, in different views. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 196, 197, 202–208; b for figs. 198–201." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542809" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542809/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 196</figureCitation>
), and pointy in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[819,985,1800,1826]" captionStart="FIGURES 196–208" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1369,1394]" captionTargetBox="[161,1376,279,1341]" captionTargetId="figure@41.[151,1388,265,1349]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 196–208. Adelopsis bruchi (Pic, 1926), 196–201, lectotype male in MNHN, from Buenos Aires. 196, aedeagus, frontal view of aedeagus apex; 197, last ventrite; 198, antenna, dorsal view; 199, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 200, protarsus and protibia; 201, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 202–206, paralectotype male in MACN (same data). 202–205, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views; 206, genital segment; 207–208, paralectotype female in MNHN (same data), spermatheca, in different views. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 196, 197, 202–208; b for figs. 198–201." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542809" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542809/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Figs. 202, 204</figureCitation>
). Flagellum thick and shorter (about 1/ 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.62" pageId="41" pageNumber="42" unit="in" value="3.0">3 in</quantity>
length) than aedeagus, with a bent apex (
<figureCitation box="[637,735,1836,1862]" captionStart="FIGURES 196–208" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1369,1394]" captionTargetBox="[161,1376,279,1341]" captionTargetId="figure@41.[151,1388,265,1349]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 196–208. Adelopsis bruchi (Pic, 1926), 196–201, lectotype male in MNHN, from Buenos Aires. 196, aedeagus, frontal view of aedeagus apex; 197, last ventrite; 198, antenna, dorsal view; 199, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 200, protarsus and protibia; 201, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 202–206, paralectotype male in MACN (same data). 202–205, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views; 206, genital segment; 207–208, paralectotype female in MNHN (same data), spermatheca, in different views. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 196, 197, 202–208; b for figs. 198–201." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542809" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542809/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 203</figureCitation>
). Proportion aedeagus/elytron = 0.27. Spiculum gastrale of the genital segment divided at apex, with long branches (
<figureCitation box="[741,838,1872,1899]" captionStart="FIGURES 196–208" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1369,1394]" captionTargetBox="[161,1376,279,1341]" captionTargetId="figure@41.[151,1388,265,1349]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 196–208. Adelopsis bruchi (Pic, 1926), 196–201, lectotype male in MNHN, from Buenos Aires. 196, aedeagus, frontal view of aedeagus apex; 197, last ventrite; 198, antenna, dorsal view; 199, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 200, protarsus and protibia; 201, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 202–206, paralectotype male in MACN (same data). 202–205, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views; 206, genital segment; 207–208, paralectotype female in MNHN (same data), spermatheca, in different views. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 196, 197, 202–208; b for figs. 198–201." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542809" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542809/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 206</figureCitation>
). Male mesotibia curved, slightly bent internally (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 196–208" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1369,1394]" captionTargetBox="[161,1376,279,1341]" captionTargetId="figure@41.[151,1388,265,1349]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 196–208. Adelopsis bruchi (Pic, 1926), 196–201, lectotype male in MNHN, from Buenos Aires. 196, aedeagus, frontal view of aedeagus apex; 197, last ventrite; 198, antenna, dorsal view; 199, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 200, protarsus and protibia; 201, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 202–206, paralectotype male in MACN (same data). 202–205, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views; 206, genital segment; 207–208, paralectotype female in MNHN (same data), spermatheca, in different views. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 196, 197, 202–208; b for figs. 198–201." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542809" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542809/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Fig. 201</figureCitation>
). Spermatheca with 3-turns placed close to the spermatheca base, followed by a short and curved body ending in a sharp curve before the elongate apical bulb (
<figureCitation box="[697,862,1944,1970]" captionStart="FIGURES 196–208" captionStartId="41.[151,264,1369,1394]" captionTargetBox="[161,1376,279,1341]" captionTargetId="figure@41.[151,1388,265,1349]" captionTargetPageId="41" captionText="FIGURES 196–208. Adelopsis bruchi (Pic, 1926), 196–201, lectotype male in MNHN, from Buenos Aires. 196, aedeagus, frontal view of aedeagus apex; 197, last ventrite; 198, antenna, dorsal view; 199, meso and metathorax, ventro-lateral view (of left side of specimen); 200, protarsus and protibia; 201, mesotarsus and mesotibia; 202–206, paralectotype male in MACN (same data). 202–205, aedeagus, left lateral, dorsal, right lateral, and ventral views; 206, genital segment; 207–208, paralectotype female in MNHN (same data), spermatheca, in different views. Scale lines = 0.5 mm; a for figs. 196, 197, 202–208; b for figs. 198–201." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3542809" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3542809/files/figure.png" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Figs. 207, 208</figureCitation>
). Proportion spermatheca/elytron = 0.12.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="41.[151,1437,1655,2043]" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis box="[199,344,1980,2006]" italics="true" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[349,465,1980,2006]" name="Argentina" pageId="41" pageNumber="42">Argentina</collectingCountry>
